title: Conditioned Wool Output for France
notes: Series Is Presented Here As Two Variables--(1)--Original Data, 1920-1925 (2)--Original Data, 1922-1939 Data Refers To Two Of The Three Principal Frence Centers For Conditioning, Rouboix And Tourcaing. Conditioning Refers To The Determination And Adjusting Of The Moisture Content. Source: Bulletin De La Statistique Generale, January 1923, P. 118, And Following Issues.
